WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.312
OMP Studio is a desktop cockpit

2
00:00:02.312 --> 00:00:04.624
for the Oh My Pi coding-agent

3
00:00:04.624 --> 00:00:06.936
harness. First, the key point: it

4
00:00:06.936 --> 00:00:09.248
drives a real coding agent, runs

5
00:00:09.248 --> 00:00:11.561
a real shell, and embeds a

6
00:00:11.561 --> 00:00:13.873
real browser, all inside one Electron

7
00:00:13.873 --> 00:00:16.185
window. It is pre-1.0, built by

8
00:00:16.185 --> 00:00:18.497
one author, and it ships for

9
00:00:18.497 --> 00:00:20.809
macOS, Linux, and Windows.

10
00:00:20.809 --> 00:00:22.818
The app gives you a single

11
00:00:22.818 --> 00:00:24.828
window to watch an agent work.

12
00:00:24.828 --> 00:00:26.837
You see its transcript, its tool

13
00:00:26.837 --> 00:00:28.846
calls, its reasoning, and its plan,

14
00:00:28.846 --> 00:00:30.855
as they happen. You can steer

15
00:00:30.855 --> 00:00:32.865
the agent mid-turn, approve tool calls,

16
00:00:32.865 --> 00:00:34.874
and drill into subagents. You can

17
00:00:34.874 --> 00:00:36.883
also open a terminal and a

18
00:00:36.883 --> 00:00:38.892
browser right beside the chat, so

19
00:00:38.892 --> 00:00:40.902
the agent's world and your own

20
00:00:40.902 --> 00:00:42.911
share the same desk.

21
00:00:42.911 --> 00:00:45.360
It is built on Electron, electron-vite,

22
00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:47.809
and React 18, all in TypeScript.

23
00:00:47.809 --> 00:00:50.259
The numbers tell the story: about

24
00:00:50.259 --> 00:00:52.708
forty-five thousand lines of source across

25
00:00:52.708 --> 00:00:55.157
two hundred twenty-seven files, one hundred

26
00:00:55.157 --> 00:00:57.606
forty-five commits, and one author, in

27
00:00:57.606 --> 00:01:00.056
under three weeks. The renderer is

28
00:01:00.056 --> 00:01:02.505
React-heavy, so TSX dominates the line

29
00:01:02.505 --> 00:01:04.954
count.

30
00:01:04.954 --> 00:01:07.638
OMP Studio uses Electron's three-process model,

31
00:01:07.638 --> 00:01:10.321
and the boundary is load-bearing. The

32
00:01:10.321 --> 00:01:13.005
main process has full host access:

33
00:01:13.005 --> 00:01:15.689
filesystem, subprocesses, the OS keychain. The

34
00:01:15.689 --> 00:01:18.372
preload is an isolated CommonJS bridge

35
00:01:18.372 --> 00:01:21.056
that publishes one curated API. The

36
00:01:21.056 --> 00:01:23.740
renderer is a sandboxed React app

37
00:01:23.740 --> 00:01:26.423
that reaches the host only through

38
00:01:26.423 --> 00:01:29.107
that typed surface, called OmpApi.

39
00:01:29.107 --> 00:01:31.357
The chat talks to the omp

40
00:01:31.357 --> 00:01:33.606
harness over an RPC bridge. The

41
00:01:33.606 --> 00:01:35.856
main process spawns omp as a

42
00:01:35.856 --> 00:01:38.106
child, writes newline-delimited JSON commands to

43
00:01:38.106 --> 00:01:40.356
its stdin, and reads JSONL frames

44
00:01:40.356 --> 00:01:42.605
from stdout. A pure session reducer

45
00:01:42.605 --> 00:01:44.855
turns those frames into render state,

46
00:01:44.855 --> 00:01:47.105
and each frame is routed to

47
00:01:47.105 --> 00:01:49.354
the right session slice. The renderer

48
00:01:49.354 --> 00:01:51.604
never spawns anything itself.

49
00:01:51.604 --> 00:01:54.082
The transcript is a virtualized list

50
00:01:54.082 --> 00:01:56.561
of content blocks: text, thinking, tool

51
00:01:56.561 --> 00:01:59.039
calls, and images. Long threads get

52
00:01:59.039 --> 00:02:01.518
a MessageScroller rail, a column of

53
00:02:01.518 --> 00:02:03.996
tick marks on the right edge

54
00:02:03.996 --> 00:02:06.474
for jumping through the conversation. The

55
00:02:06.474 --> 00:02:08.953
active tick tracks the topmost visible

56
00:02:08.953 --> 00:02:11.431
message, and clicks go through Virtuoso's

57
00:02:11.431 --> 00:02:13.910
index scroller, because virtualization means the

58
00:02:13.910 --> 00:02:16.389
target row may not be mounted.

59
00:02:16.389 --> 00:02:18.434
The shell supports up to eight

60
00:02:18.434 --> 00:02:20.480
split panes. Each pane can hold

61
00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:22.525
a chat, a file view, or

62
00:02:22.525 --> 00:02:24.571
a subagent drill-in, and you can

63
00:02:24.571 --> 00:02:26.616
drag and dock them. A hot-and-cold

64
00:02:26.616 --> 00:02:28.661
split keeps pane ids cold in

65
00:02:28.661 --> 00:02:30.707
the store, while each transcript pane

66
00:02:30.707 --> 00:02:32.752
subscribes to its own live session

67
00:02:32.752 --> 00:02:34.798
slice. The left sidebar anchors on

68
00:02:34.798 --> 00:02:36.842
the open worktree and branch.

69
00:02:36.842 --> 00:02:39.156
Six read-only panels surface the agent's

70
00:02:39.156 --> 00:02:41.470
world: skills, MCP servers, agents, models

71
00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:43.784
and providers, GitHub, and Linear. Each

72
00:02:43.784 --> 00:02:46.098
is a main-process reader that degrades

73
00:02:46.098 --> 00:02:48.412
gracefully to empty when its source

74
00:02:48.412 --> 00:02:50.725
is missing. That graceful degradation is

75
00:02:50.725 --> 00:02:53.039
why the app, the unit tests,

76
00:02:53.039 --> 00:02:55.353
and the e2e smoke all run

77
00:02:55.353 --> 00:02:57.667
without the omp harness or gh

78
00:02:57.667 --> 00:02:59.981
installed.

79
00:02:59.981 --> 00:03:02.118
The trust model is the point.

80
00:03:02.118 --> 00:03:04.255
The renderer never touches the host

81
00:03:04.255 --> 00:03:06.392
directly and never loads remote content.

82
00:03:06.392 --> 00:03:08.529
The two capabilities that touch untrusted

83
00:03:08.529 --> 00:03:10.666
content, the terminal and the embedded

84
00:03:10.666 --> 00:03:12.803
browser, are isolated in their own

85
00:03:12.803 --> 00:03:14.939
sandboxed contexts and off by default.

86
00:03:14.939 --> 00:03:17.076
The terminal runs a real shell

87
00:03:17.076 --> 00:03:19.213
at user privilege, but the agent

88
00:03:19.213 --> 00:03:21.350
never drives it. The browser loads

89
00:03:21.350 --> 00:03:23.487
remote pages in a separate view

90
00:03:23.487 --> 00:03:25.625
with no IPC bridge.

91
00:03:25.625 --> 00:03:27.856
Two recent tools harden the workflow.

92
00:03:27.856 --> 00:03:30.087
The demo recorder, npm run demo,

93
00:03:30.087 --> 00:03:32.318
launches the built app against hermetic

94
00:03:32.318 --> 00:03:34.549
fixtures and stitches an mp4 with

95
00:03:34.549 --> 00:03:36.780
ffmpeg, so a pull request can

96
00:03:36.780 --> 00:03:39.010
attach proof of a UI behavior.

97
00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:41.241
The sync-check script is a read-only

98
00:03:41.241 --> 00:03:43.472
drift radar: it flags stale branches,

99
00:03:43.472 --> 00:03:45.703
missing worktrees, and open pull request

100
00:03:45.703 --> 00:03:47.934
state, and it only ever prints

101
00:03:47.934 --> 00:03:50.165
suggestions.

102
00:03:50.165 --> 00:03:52.356
The gates are deliberate. Biome handles

103
00:03:52.356 --> 00:03:54.547
lint and format in one tool.

104
00:03:54.547 --> 00:03:56.737
tsc runs two typecheck projects split

105
00:03:56.737 --> 00:03:58.928
along the process boundary. Vitest covers

106
00:03:58.928 --> 00:04:01.119
the renderer, bun test covers node-side

107
00:04:01.119 --> 00:04:03.310
logic and the pure reducer, and

108
00:04:03.310 --> 00:04:05.501
Playwright runs the e2e smoke against

109
00:04:05.501 --> 00:04:07.692
the built app. A release is

110
00:04:07.692 --> 00:04:09.882
one command plus a tag push,

111
00:04:09.882 --> 00:04:12.073
and CI cuts the GitHub Release

112
00:04:12.073 --> 00:04:14.264
with notes pulled from the changelog.

113
00:04:14.264 --> 00:04:16.618
You can remember OMP Studio as

114
00:04:16.618 --> 00:04:18.973
a typed, sandboxed Electron app that

115
00:04:18.973 --> 00:04:21.327
turns the omp harness into a

116
00:04:21.327 --> 00:04:23.682
desk you can actually sit at.

117
00:04:23.682 --> 00:04:26.036
It is young, fast-moving, and already

118
00:04:26.036 --> 00:04:28.391
a full interactive cockpit: a virtualized

119
00:04:28.391 --> 00:04:30.745
chat, a real terminal, a sandboxed

120
00:04:30.745 --> 00:04:33.100
browser, and six read-only panels, all

121
00:04:33.100 --> 00:04:35.454
behind one locked-down renderer.
